          <msContents>
            <summary>Apocryphal story and didactic poem about the meeting of the Advaita Vedāntan sage Śaṅkarācārya with an untouchable (dalit) man who turns out to be the Hindu god Śiva and their ensuing conversation about the nature of the Self, the body, and caste. Manuscript contains a commentary running above and below the root text.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Manīṣāpañcaka</title>
              <author>Śaṅkarācārya,</author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīmparamahaṃsaparivrājakācāryaśrīmadgoviṃdabhagavatpūjyapādaśiṣyaśrīmacchaṃkarācāryakṛtamanīṣāpaṃcakasya madhumaṃjarī ṭIkā saṃpūrṇā // oṃ tat sat // śubhaṃ bhavatu // (f. 7r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
